<item>
            <title>[NET-440] library throws an exception in case the SYST command is not known or the result is not known by the implementation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-440</link>
                <project id="12310487" key="NET">Commons Net</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The FTP client uses the SYST command to determine the list output.&lt;br/&gt;
This can fail in two ways:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a ParserInitializationException in case the response of the server is not known by apache.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the response to SYST command is 502 command unknown (the command is optional after all - &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc959.txt&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc959.txt&lt;/a&gt;) the client throws an IOException.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Can&apos;t it just default to UNIX for these type of ftp servers?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
